# 🍔 CraveCave – Online Food Ordering Website

Welcome to **CraveCave**, a full-stack web application that allows users to explore, filter, and order delicious food online from various restaurants. This project was built using **PHP**, **MySQL**, **HTML**, **CSS**, and **JavaScript** as part of an academic web development project.

![CraveCave Banner](https://LogoImage.jpg) <!-- Replace with your own hosted image if needed -->

---

## 🚀 Features

- 🔐 **User Authentication** (Admin, Restaurant Manager, Customer)
- 🍱 **Food Categories & Dynamic Filtering**
- 🛒 **Add to Cart** & Place Orders (Cash on Delivery)
- 🧾 **Order Summary and Management**
- 🧑‍🍳 **Restaurant Panel** – Manage menu, view orders
- 📊 **Admin Dashboard** – Manage users, restaurants, and food items
- 📱 **Mobile-Friendly UI** with custom styling and animations

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

| Layer        | Technologies                    |
|-------------|----------------------------------|
| Frontend     | HTML, CSS, JavaScript            |
| Backend      | PHP (Core PHP – Procedural)      |
| Database     | MySQL                            |
| Server       | XAMPP (Apache, MySQL)            |

---

## 📂 Project Structure

/foodorderr
├── admin/ # Admin dashboard
├── images/ # Image assets
├── restaurant/ # Restaurant manager panel
├── user/ # Customer pages (login, menu, cart)
├── includes/ # Database connections and utilities
├── css/ # Stylesheets
├── js/ # JavaScript files
├── index.php # Homepage
└── README.md



---



## 💡 How to Run Locally

1. Download or clone this repo:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/foodorderr.git
2.Move the folder to your XAMPP htdocs directory.

3. Start Apache and MySQL in XAMPP control panel.

4. Import the SQL file into phpMyAdmin:
      Database Name: foodorder
      Import → foodorder.sql from /db or root

5. Open your browser:
     http://localhost/foodorderr/


